== 3. Nf3? · Roscher gambit ==
The Roscher gambit is an unsound gambit in the Pirc. White allows Black to take on e4.

After '''3...Nxe4''' 4. Bd3 Nf6 then e.g. 5. c4, White hopes for development in compensation for the loss of their central pawn, but this is thought to be insufficient.

Black can decline with '''3...g6''' and White has nothing better than to [[Chess Opening Theory/1. e4/1...d6/2. d4/2...Nf6/3. Nc3/3...g6/4. Nf3|transpose into the Classical Pirc]] with 4. Nc3. 

=== History ===
An early record of this line is from [[Wikipedia:Charles Jaffe|Charles Jaffé]] (1879―1941). It is named for Joerg Roscher, who played it in the '80s.<ref>[https://www.chessgames.com/perl/chessgame?gid=1243637 Roscher v Plath, 1989 - Chessgames.com]</ref>

